flavor_text_entries.ruby:
LOUDRED’s bellowing can completely
decimate a wood-frame house. It uses
its voice to punish its foes. This POKéMON’s round ears serve as
loudspeakers.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
LOUDRED shouts while stamping its feet.
After it finishes shouting, this
POKéMON becomes incapable of hearing anything for a while. This is considered
to be a weak point.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
It positions the round speakers on its
head to assail foes with ultrasonic waves
at massive volume. It builds power by
stomping the ground.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
When it stamps its feet and bellows, it
generates ultrasonic waves that can blow
apart a house.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
Loudred’s ears serve as speakers, and they can
put out sound waves powerful enough to blow
away a house.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
The force of this Pokémon’s loud voice isn’t just
the sound—it’s also the wave of air pressure that
blows opponents away and damages them.
